class Ratio:
    def __init__(self):
        print('start calculating the yield of each stocks')
    
    def yield_calculator(self,xx_price):
        '''
        : xx_price
        : 
        :: yield_code()yield_period
        '''
        yield_code  = []
        yield_period = []
        
    
        for name,group in xx_price.groupby('code'):
            yield_code.append(name)
            x = []
            for i in range(1,len(group)):
                x.append(round((group['close'][group.index[i]]-group['close'][group.index[i-1]])/group['close'][group.index[i-1]]*100,2))
                #
            yield_period.append(x)

        return yield_code, yield_period  
    
    def yield_calculator_in(self,xx_price):
        '''
        : xx_price
        : 
        :: yield_code()yield_period
        '''
        yield_code  = []
        yield_period = []
        
    
        for name,group in xx_price.groupby('code'):
            yield_code.append(name)
            x = []
            for i in range(1,len(group)):
                x.append(round(100*math.log(group['close'][group.index[i]]/group['close'][group.index[i-1]]),2))
                #
            yield_period.append(x)

        return yield_code, yield_period

    def yield_total(self,yield_period):
        '''
        : yield_period
        : 
        :: total_mean
        '''
        total_mean = np.nanmean(yield_period, axis = 0)

        return total_mean

    def yield_displot(self,xx_daily_mean,xx_name,period):
        '''
        : xx_daily_mean(),xx_name,period 
        : 
        '''
        sns.set_style("whitegrid")
        plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))#

        sns.distplot(xx_daily_mean, rug=False, bins=50, color="blue",fit=norm,kde_kws={"color": "red", "lw": 2.5, 'linestyle':'--'},
        label = f'{xx_name}{period}')

        # xx_daily
        plt.axvline(xx_daily_mean.mean(),color='b',linestyle="-",alpha=1)
        plt.text(xx_daily_mean.mean(),0.05,f'{xx_name}{period}:{round(xx_daily_mean.mean(),2)}%' ,fontproperties = 'SimHei') 
        plt.title(f"{xx_name}{period}",fontproperties = 'SimHei') 

    def yield_test(self,xx_name,period,xx_daily_mean,xx_daily_mean_in):
        '''
        : xx_name()period,xx_daily_mean()xx_daily_mean_in
        : 
        :: 
        '''
        print(f'{xx_name}{period}'
           '\n',round(kurtosis(xx_daily_mean, axis=0, fisher=True, bias=True, nan_policy='propagate'),5), 
           '\n',round(skew(xx_daily_mean, axis=0, bias=True, nan_policy='propagate'),5), 
           '\nKS',kstest(xx_daily_mean, 'norm', args=(), N=20, alternative='two-sided', mode='auto'), 
           '\n'
           )
        print(f'{xx_name}{period}'
           '\n',round(kurtosis(xx_daily_mean_in, axis=0, fisher=True, bias=True, nan_policy='propagate'),5), 
           '\n',round(skew(xx_daily_mean_in, axis=0, bias=True, nan_policy='propagate'),5), 
           '\nKS',kstest(xx_daily_mean_in, 'norm', args=(), N=20, alternative='two-sided', mode='auto'), 
           '\n'
           )

class Excess:
    def __init__(self):
        print('start calculating the excess rate of each stocks')

    def Excess_earnings(self,xx_code,xx_daily,xx_daily_mean):
        '''
        : xx_code,xx_daily*,xx_daily_mean
        : 
        :: 
        '''
        excess_daily = []
        win = []
        for i in range(len(xx_code)):
            excess_daily.append(list(map(lambda x: round(x[0]-x[1],2), zip(xx_daily[i], xx_daily_mean)))) #
        for i in range(len(xx_code)):
            win.append(round(np.sum(np.array(excess_daily[i])>0)/len(xx_daily_mean)*100,2)) #,

        return excess_daily,win

    def Excess_test(self,excess_daily):
        '''
        : excess_daily(*)
        :        
        ::       
        '''
        test_mean = []
        test_variance = []
        test_kurtosis = []
        test_skew = []
        for i in range(len(excess_daily)):
            test_mean.append(np.round(np.nanmean(excess_daily[i]),2))
        for i in range(len(excess_daily)):
            test_variance.append(np.round(np.nanvar(excess_daily[i]),2))
        for i in range(len(excess_daily)):
            test_kurtosis.append(np.round(kurtosis(excess_daily[i], axis=0, fisher=True, bias=True, nan_policy='omit'),3))
        for i in range(len(excess_daily)):
            test_skew.append(np.round(skew(excess_daily[i], axis=0, bias=True, nan_policy='omit'),3))
        
        return test_mean, test_variance, test_kurtosis, test_skew

    def Max_win(self,xx_code,win):
        '''
        : xx_code(),win
        :  
        ::  
        '''
        return xx_code[np.argmax(np.array(win))], np.max(np.array(win))

    def Excess_plot(self,xx_code,test_mean, test_variance, win):
        '''
        : xx_code,test_mean, test_variance, win
        :      
        ::      
        '''
        external_stylesheets = ['https://codepen.io/chriddyp/pen/bWLwgP.css']
        app = JupyterDash(__name__, external_stylesheets=external_stylesheets)

        # Create server variable with Flask server object for use with gunicorn
        server = app.server
        #!!! !!! !!!

        df_excess = pd.DataFrame(
            {'code': xx_code,
            'mean': test_mean, 
            'variance': test_variance, 
            'win': win}
        )

        app.layout = html.Div([
                     dcc.Graph(id="scatter-plot"),
                     html.P("mean:"),
                     dcc.RangeSlider(
                     id='range-slider',
                     min=-0.5, max=1, step=0.1,
                     marks={-0.5: '-0.5', 1: '1'},
                     value=[-0.5, 1]
                     ),
                ])
        @app.callback(
                Output("scatter-plot", "figure"), 
                [Input("range-slider", "value")])
        def update_bar_chart(slider_range):
            low, high = slider_range
            mask = (df_excess['mean'] > low) & (df_excess['mean'] < high)
            fig = px.scatter(
                df_excess[mask], x="variance", y="mean", 
                color="code", size='win', 
                )
            return fig

        app.run_server(mode="inline",host=os.getenv("HOST", "127.0.0.2"))
